===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[expensive]]; [[costly]]
#: {{ant|zh|廉|賤}}
#: {{zh-x|那 件 衣服 很 貴，是 綢子{zi} 的。|That dress is '''expensive'''. It's made of silk.}}
# [[precious]]; [[valuable]]
#: {{zh-x|可貴|valuable}}
#: {{zh-x|貴金屬|precious metal}}
#* {{zh-x|民 為{wéi} 貴，社稷 次 之，君 為{wéi} 輕。|The people are the most important element in a nation; the spirits of the land and grain are the next; the sovereign is the lightest.|ref=Mencius}}
# [[superior]]; [[noble]]
#: {{zh-x|貴族|nobility}}
#* {{zh-x|富 與 貴 是 人 之 所 欲 也，不 以 其 道 得 之，不 處 也；貧 與 賤 是 人 之 所 惡 也，不 以 其 道 得 之，不 去 也。|Riches and honors are what men desire. If it cannot be obtained in the proper way, they should not be held. Poverty and meanness are what men dislike. If it cannot be avoided in the proper way, they should not be avoided. |ref=Analects}}
# to [[regard]] as [[valuable]]
#: {{zh-x|成功 貴 在 堅持|Perseverance is vital to success.}}
#: {{zh-x|人 貴 有 自知之明|A smart man knows how little he knows.}}
# {{lb|zh|humble}} [[your]] {{gloss|to a deity, person or establishment}}
#: {{zh-x|貴國|your country}}
#: {{zh-x|您 貴姓？|What is '''your''' surname?}}
#: {{zh-x|能否 給 我 些 貴 公司 更 詳細 的 資料？|Could you give me more details about '''your''' company?}}
# {{zh-short|貴州}}
#: {{zh-x|^雲貴|Yunnan and Guizhou}}
# {{surname|zh}}

====Synonyms====
{{zh-dial|貴}}

====Usage notes====
In Hong Kong and Taiwan, a space is often left before this word when it is used as a humble term of "your" to show respect when writing formal letters, and this practice is known as {{zh-l|抬頭}}. This practice, however, is not common in Mainland China.

